[SN]TITLE[SN]
Three injured in collision at Crickhowell on A40

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Three people have been injured in a collision involving two vehicles on the A40 at Crickhowell.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
A Mid and West Wales Fire Service spokesman said they were called to the crash at the Manor Hotel at 14:45 GMT.
A man was airlifted to hospital and there were two other casualties, he said.
Crews from Crickhowell and Abergavenny are there. Traffic Wales says the A40 between Crickhowell and Bwlch is closed in both directions.
